annotationA: Histone methyltransferase activity; protein-arginine omega-N asymmetric methyltransferase activity; histone methyltransferase activity (H4-R3 specific); protein-arginine omega-N monomethyltransferase activity; protein-arginine N-methyltransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: histone H4-R3 methylation; peptidyl-arginine methylation, to asymmetrical-dimethyl arginine; histone methylation
annotationB: DNA-binding protein modulo; Its capacity to bind DNA and protein(s), and its differential expression during development suggest a role in the regulation of gene expression during Drosophila development. It could, in interaction with other factors, be required for the translation of instructions provided by pattern forming genes and controls, via chromatin changes, the activity of genes critical for the process of morphogenesis of several embryonic territories
